Seventh Avenue South, west side, south of Barrow Street.
August 10, 1927.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

North on Seventh Avenue South, from Barrow Street.
March 29, 1928.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

31-25 Barrow Street, adjoining and East of the S. E. corner of Seventh Ave (Extension). Prominent building is the Greenwich House, a community settlement project, with a 3-story frame house (No. 25), adjoining.  View shown is across Seventh Ave.

Barrow Street, eastern section (formerly Reason Street), west from Seventh Avenue South. The S.W. corner of Barrow and Bleeker Streets was cut off when Seventh Avenue South was put through in 1915.

May 27, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

Seventh Ave., west side, south from and including Barrow Street. Also shown is Barrow Street, south side, west from Seventh Ave., to, but not including Bedford Street.

March 29, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

Seventh Avenue, (left) at the N. E. corner of Barrow Street (right) showing a gas station which formerly occupied property belonging to two separate owners. Because of difficulties the tenant was dispossessed from the corner plot and the owner had same fenced in. A story giving details was recently carried in either the New York Sun or Times.

VIEW 2 is another angle of same scene.

September 16, 1938
Views 1 and 2

George D. Chinn

Seventh Avenue, (left) at the N. E. corner of Barrow Street (right) showing a gas station which formerly occupied property belonging to two separate owners. Because of difficulties the tenant was dispossessed from the corner plot and the owner had same fenced in. A story giving details was recently carried in either the New York Sun or Times.

VIEW 2 is another angle of same scene.

September 16, 1938
Views 1 and 2

George D. Chinn

Barrow Street, at, adjoining and east of the S. E. corner of Seventh Avenue, showing prominently the Greenwich House.  This bears No. 27-31 Barrow Street.  The photographer vantage point is at Bleecker Street and he is viewing across the Avenue.
1939-40
Alexander Alland, photo
